final_hyps.green: The green object is the Goal that the agent must reach.
final_hyps.brown: Brown objects are False Walls. The agent can move through False Walls.
final_hyps.yellow: The yellow object is a Key. The agent can pick up the Key by moving into its space. While holding the Key, the agent is colored purple.
final_hyps.cyan: The cyan object is a KeyDoor. When the agent moves onto this object, the KeyDoor opens and the Key is destroyed. The agent cannot move through the KeyDoor while it is closed.

solve_plan: First determine that the green object is the Goal object. Because the cyan object is a KeyDoor at (18, 8) and the goal object is at (19, 9), the agent must obtain the yellow Key to open the KeyDoor. Align the agent on the horizontal axis (x=13) by moving RIGHT. Because the agent is at x=5, it must move RIGHT 13 - 5 = 8 times. Next, pick up the Key by moving DOWN. Because the agent and the Key are at the same y-coordinate (y=8), no movement in the y-direction is needed. Then, move to the KeyDoor at (18, 8) by moving RIGHT. Because the agent has moved to x=13, it must move RIGHT 18 - 13 = 5 times. Next, open the KeyDoor by moving DOWN. Because the agent and the KeyDoor are at the same y-coordinate (y=8), no movement in the y-direction is needed. Finally, move to reach the goal (x=19, y=9) by first moving UP once, then moving RIGHT once.
